 &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<table><thead><tr><th class="Criteria">Criteria</th><th class="node-js"><div>Best Architecture Style</div></th><th class="node-js"><div>Reasons</div></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Scalability</td><td class="font-weight-500">REST, gRPC</td><td class="font-weight-500">REST's statelessness ensures scalability; gRPC's multiplexing optimizes resource usage.</td></tr><tr><td>Real-Time Communication</td><td class="font-weight-500">WebSockets, gRPC</td><td class="font-weight-500">WebSockets support persistent connections; gRPC offers bidirectional streaming for real-time use.</td></tr><tr><td>Data Efficiency</td><td class="font-weight-500">GraphQL, MQTT</td><td class="font-weight-500">GraphQL avoids over-fetching by fetching exact data; MQTT's lightweight protocol is ideal for loT.</td></tr><tr><td>Security</td><td class="font-weight-500">SOAP</td><td class="font-weight-500">SOAP includes robust security features like WS-Security for encrypted, authenticated communication.</td></tr><tr><td>Low Latency</td><td class="font-weight-500">gRPC, WebSockets</td><td class="font-weight-500">gRPC's efficient serialization and WebSockets' full-duplex communication ensure minimal delay.</td></tr><tr><td>Interoperability</td><td class="font-weight-500">SOAP</td><td class="font-weight-500">SOAP adheres to strict standards, making it suitable for enterprise-level cross- platform integration.</td></tr><tr><td>loT Applications</td><td class="font-weight-500">MQTT</td><td class="font-weight-500">MQTT's lightweight design and pub/sub model excel in constrained, unreliable networks.</td></tr><tr><td>Complex Data Relationships</td><td class="font-weight-500">GraphQL</td><td class="font-weight-500">GraphQL's query language handles complex, interrelated data structures efficiently.</td></tr><tr><td>Simple CRUD Operations</td><td class="font-weight-500">REST</td><td class="font-weight-500">REST's straightforward approach is well-suited for basic resource operations.</td></tr><tr><td class="lastrow-first-td">Enterprise Transactions</td><td class="font-weight-500">SOAP</td><td class="last-row-td font-weight-500">SOAP's support for ACID transactions ensures reliability in enterprise systems.</td></tr></tbody></table>
